n, England":"Berrynarbor, Devon, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Berry","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Irish and Manx: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Béara</b> ‘descendant of <i>Béara</i>’, a personal name of unexplained etymology; or, in some cases, perhaps an Anglicized form of Irish and Manx <b>Ó Beargha</b>. Compare   Barry   1.","Scottish and northern Irish: variant of   Barrie  .","English: habitational name from any of several places called in Devon named with Old English <i>byrig</i>, dative case of <i>burh</i> ‘fortified manor house, stronghold’, such as Berry Pomeroy and Berrynarbor."],"variants":[{"name":"Berrey","meanings":["English: variant of   Berry  ."]},{"name":"Barry","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Donal, Aidan, Ciaran, Eoin, John Patrick, Kaitlin, Kieran, Murphy, Aileen, Brigid, Caitlin.","Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Beargha</b> ‘descendant of <i>Beargh</i>’, a byname meaning ‘plunderer’.","Irish and Manx: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Báire</b> ‘descendant of <i>Báire</i>’, a short form of either of two Gaelic personal names, <i>Bairrfhionn</i> or <i>Fionnbharr</i>, both meaning ‘fair-topped’. This may also be the source of the Manx name <i>Barry</i>, whose family's main seat was Ballavarry in Kirk Andreas."]},{"name":"Bery","meanings":["English: variant of   Berry  .","Hungarian (<b>Béry</b>): habitational name for someone from any of various places called Bér, in Baranya, Komárom, Nógrád, Pest, Vas, or Zala counties."]},{"name":"Beery","meanings":["Irish: Anglicized form of <b>Ó Béara</b>. See   Berry   and   O'Berry  .","Americanized form of Swiss German   Bieri  ."]},{"name":"Berrie","meanings":["Scottish:","(Glasgow): from Middle English or Older Scots <i>(atte) beri</i> ‘(at the) manor house’, see   Berry  .","variant   Barrie  ."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When John Berry was born about 1390, in Berrynarbor, Devon, England, his father, William Berry, was 25 and his mother, Isabel De Penrise, was 13. He had at least 2 sons and 1 daughter with Margaret Giffard. He died about 1433, in his hometown, at the age of 45."},"et":{"about 1390–about 1433":"umbes 1390–umbes 1433","1390–1433":"1390–1433","1390–Female":"1390–Surnud","1390–1419":"1390–1419","1419–1470":"1419–1470","1422–1464":"1422–1464","1423–1479":"1423–1479","–Male":"Surnud","1367–1396":"1367–1396","1379–Female":"1379–Surnud","about 1390":"umbes 1390","1396":"1396","1470":"1470","1390":"1390","about 1419":"umbes 1419","1479":"1479","1423":"1423","1379":"1379","1422":"1422","1367":"1367","1433":"1433","1464":"1464","about 1433":"umbes 1433","about 1396":"umbes 1396","1419":"1419","Berrynarbor, Devon, England":"Berrynarbor, Devon, England"},"fi":{"about 1390–about 1433":"noin 1390–noin 1433","1390–1433":"1390–1433","1390–Female":"1390–Kuollut","1390–1419":"1390–1419","1419–1470":"1419–1470","1422–1464":"1422–1464","1423–1479":"1423–1479","–Male":"Kuollut","1367–1396":"1367–1396","1379–Female":"1379–Kuollut","about 1390":"noin 1390","1396":"1396","1470":"1470","1390":"1390","about 1419":"noin 1419","1479":"1479","1423":"1423","1379":"1379","1422":"1422","1367":"1367","1433":"1433","1464":"1464","about 1433":"noin 1433","about 1396":"noin 1396","1419":"1419","Berrynarbor, Devon, England":"Berrynarbor, Devon, England"},"fr":{"about 1390–about 1433":"environ 1390–environ 1433","1390–1433":"1390–1433","1390–Female":"1390–Décédée","1390–1419":"1390–1419","1419–1470":"1419–1470","1422–1464":"1422–1464","1423–1479":"1423–1479","–Male":"Décédé","1367–1396":"1367–1396","1379–Female":"1379–Décédée","about 1390":"environ 1390","1396":"1396","1470":"1470","1390":"1390","about 1419":"environ 1419","1479":"1479","1423":"1423","1379":"1379","1422":"1422","1367":"1367","1433":"1433","1464":"1464","about 1433":"environ 1433